<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-16473] KafkaDockerWrapper uses wrong cluster ID when formatting log dir</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16473</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a bug in &lt;tt&gt;KafkaDockerWrapper&lt;/tt&gt;, that causes &lt;tt&gt;Some(&amp;lt;value of CLUSTER_ID environment variable&amp;gt;)&lt;/tt&gt; to be used when formatting the log dir when Kafka is started for the first time inside a Docker container.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More specifically, the problem is in &lt;tt&gt;formatStorageCmd&lt;/tt&gt;: The code uses &lt;tt&gt;env.get(&quot;CLUSTER_ID&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt;, but this returns an &lt;tt&gt;Option&lt;/tt&gt; not a &lt;tt&gt;String&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code should instead check whether the environment variable is set, raising an exception if it is not set.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
